        <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Jamaica</ENAMEX> there were <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">approximately 100,000</NUMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">Arawak</ENAMEX> living on the island.
        They called <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">Jamaica ‚ÄúXaymaca‚Äù (‚</ENAMEX>Äúland of <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">wood</ENAMEX> and water‚Äù).
        <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Columbus</ENAMEX> and the Arrival of Europeans
